# __PROJECT_NAME__

An MCP server with embedded Meter billing. Each tool call reserves prepaid
credits, runs, then commits the actual price; an insufficient balance returns
`payment_required` instead of running for free.

## Run it

```bash
npm run dev
```

The server listens on `http://localhost:8787/mcp`. In another terminal, call a
tool through the Meter CLI (the caller identifies the buyer with an
`x-customer-id` header, which `meter call` sends as `--customer`):

```bash
meter call echo --url http://localhost:8787/mcp --args '{"text":"hi"}'
```

Then watch the usage events land in your Meter service:

```bash
meter events tail
```

## Switching to the Meter gateway

The commands above call this server directly. To put Meter's hosted gateway in
front of it — so credit checks, auto-recharge, and customer auth run at the
edge instead of in this process — deploy this server, then point your service's
integration at its URL:

```bash
meter integration update --upstream-url <deployed URL> --gateway-enabled true
```

Callers then hit the gateway URL, and Meter forwards paid, authenticated
requests upstream to this server.
